$ chexa8_free_thermal.bdf
$ Single CHEXA8 unit cube — free thermal expansion with zero stress
$
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      minimal — all compatible with free-expansion field
$           u = alpha*dT*x,  v = alpha*dT*y,  w = alpha*dT*z
$   fix T3 of all bottom-face nodes (w=0 at z=0 ✓)
$   fix T1+T2 of node 1 (at origin, u=v=0 ✓)
$   fix T2 of node 2 (at (1,0,0), v=0 ✓)
$
$ Expected (alpha*dT = 1e-5 * 100 = 1e-3):
$   Top-face z-displacement = 1e-3 m
$   Node 6 at (1,0,1): u = 1e-3 m, w = 1e-3 m
$   Node 7 at (1,1,1): u = 1e-3 m, v = 1e-3 m, w = 1e-3 m
$   Stress ≈ 0 (trilinear element represents linear field exactly)
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CHEXA8 FREE THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: unit cube
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,5,,0.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,6,,1.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,7,,1.0,1.0,1.0
GRID,8,,0.0,1.0,1.0
$ Material: alpha = 1e-5 /°C
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
$ Solid property
PSOLID,1,1
$ Single CHEXA8
CHEXA,1,1,1,2,3,4,5,6,+
+,7,8
$ Minimal BCs (all compatible with free-expansion field)
SPC1,1,3,1
SPC1,1,3,2
SPC1,1,3,3
SPC1,1,3,4
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C on all nodes
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
TEMP,1,5,100.0
TEMP,1,6,100.0
TEMP,1,7,100.0
TEMP,1,8,100.0
ENDDATA
